</p>


<!--
<div class="card-block">
<h2>Features</h2>

<ul>
<li>Coding and describing visual and audio information using an integrated playback</li>
<li>Frame-by-frame mode</li>
<li>Configuration of unlimited number of subjects and behaviors</li>
<li>Definition of an unlimited number of independent variables (text, numeric, set of values)</li>
<li>Up to 2 media files can be synchronously played (with positive or negative offset)</li>
<li>Coding of media files at various playback speeds</li>
<li><a href="/static/screenshots2/spectrogram.png">Sound spectrogram visualization</a></li>
<li>Media files can be enqueue for playing, the event time will be the cumulative over all media.
<li><a href="static/screenshots2/time_budget.png">Time budget analysis</a></li>
<li><a href="static/screenshots2/plot_events.png">Graphical representation of coded data</a></li>
<li><a href="static/screenshots2/geometric_measurements.png">Geometric measurements (distance, area and angle)</a></li>
<li>Exporting coded data in various formats (TSV, CSV, ODS, XLS, SQL)</li>
<li>Use of open format for storing data (JSON) to allow further analysis</li>
</ul>
<a href="http://olivierfriard.github.io/BORIS/pages/features.html">All features</a>


